    body: "Equiprobabilism is the median position championed by St. Alphonsus Liguori, the patron of moral theologians. When the opinion favoring liberty and the opinion favoring the law are genuinely equal in probability, a doubtful law does not bind (lex dubia non obligat), and one may follow liberty. But when the opinion favoring the law is notably more probable, one must follow it. This system absorbs the best insights of both probabilism (respect for liberty) and probabiliorism (respect for law) while avoiding their extremes. It became the dominant approach in Catholic moral theology after Alphonsus's canonization and his declaration as a Doctor of the Church.",
